    "body": "There's no external documentation about this, but it's documented within the code. Look at `trie.go`, for example. The trie nodes reference other trie nodes, and 'expands' as needed. So if you have only a root, and you try to walk it down a certain path, it will resolve nodes from the database as needed. \r\n\r\n> I'm wondering because state.New() could find trie for genesis block but can't for the most recent.\r\n\r\nThat sounds like you're not yet synced. If you are not finished with your fast-sync, your node will report a certain block as being the most recent, but all state is not finished downloading: this will have an incomplete state-trie. \r\n",
